parameters:
Haa... haa... The stairs were so long... It's
already this dark...

...After we finish praying, let's hurry and go
shopping.

God... I don't care what happens to me, please
cure Haru's illness...

??? Hmm, as long as 'Haru-kun' is saved, it
doesn't matter what happens to you, right?

Yes... For Haru-kun's sake, I am willing to endure
any hardship...

??? Well done for coming... descendant of
Nagatsuki bloodline... My name is

??? Don't be afraid... Listen carefully... My name
is

Um...? The belly button?! I have to hide my belly
button!!?
Being teased by a ghost...!? Eeekkk!!

??? What the hell are you doing since earlier!!
Making fun of people and calling them ghosts and
stuff!!

??? Don't you think it's rude to someone you just
met?!! Seriously... Young people these days, can't
even reach 80 like this... *mumbling*

But... um... with that kind of appearance, I
thought you were a ghost...

??? Hm? I've died once before, you know. That's
why I'm like a ghost now, hahaha♪

??? By the way, going all the way to this desolate
shrine with a solemn face... do you have something
troubling you?

??? Just by confiding in someone, you can feel
relieved, you know? Come on, give it a try.

(.....Somehow, a really bizarre ghost? But you
don't seem bad, and if it's just talking a
little...)
??? I see, your son... that's unfortunate...
Well... so what should I do...
??? Hmm... Well, I do have some idea about that.
Wha?! I-Is that true?! Please tell me!!?

??? Ahem... The condition of your son... It is
likely due to my weakened power and your
bloodline.
What... do you mean by that?

??? I have been protecting this land as a guardian
deity for a long time.
So you were a ghost... a god, huh...

??? Indeed, you should show respect. And beings
like myself gain power from the faith of the
people.

??? Well... as you can see from the state of this
shrine, the people's faith has been diminishing...

??? Because of that, my spiritual power has
weakened, and negative energy... gloominess has
been increasing in this land.

??? ...And another thing, your bloodline easily
attracts that gloominess onto me.

??? 'You have matured, and it seems you naturally
have a strong resistance to gloominess.'

??? However, your son is still young, so his
resistance is weak and he cannot resist the
gloominess. That's why he has fallen asleep.

If that's the case... then a doctor won't be able
to cure him, right?

??? 'If you team up with me and regain your
spiritual power, you will be able to save your
son.'

...I will do it. Let me assist you in regaining
your spiritual power!

??? '...An immediate answer, huh. Is it okay even
if you don't know what I'm going to do?'

Yes, if there is even a slight possibility of that
child getting better...! I will do my best!!

??? Hehehe... That's a good response! Well then,
let's proceed with the necessary ritual, shall we?
Are you ready?

??? 'Nyam nyam nyam nyam nyam... Somehow or
another.... Ah... I remember.... Laputa
Ketaaba.... Oceanic... The next thing is...
umm.......... Disappeeeearrr!!!'
(It feels like I gave up halfway...)

??? Haa... haa... haa... With this, our souls are
now connected...

??? By this, you will be appreciated by others...
Somehow or another, my power will be restored.

I see... So, because our souls are recognized as
the same, indirectly the ghosts will also be
appreciated and as a result, faith will
increase... Is that the idea?

??? Yes! Yes! That's it! That's what I wanted to
say!

??? ....At that time, I still hadn't said my name.
I don't want to be called a ghost forever.

Ah... come to think of it.... My name is Ayako
Nagatsuki. Nice to meet you.
??? Hmm, Ayako, that's a good name.

Some people in town also call you Eternal Spirit-
sama.

Feel free to call me 'Rei-sama' or something like
that.

(It's not much different from being called a
ghost...)

Well then, Ayako. Shall we go gather gratitude for
the Potato Faith right away?

(But... I wonder if we'll really find someone in
need so conveniently...?)
